{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.«tactic#find_»\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Find</span>.<span class=\"name\">«tactic#find_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`#find t` finds definitions and theorems whose result type matches the term `t`, and prints them as\ninfo lines. Use holes in `t` to indicate arbitrary subexpressions, for example `#find _ ∧ _` will\nmatch any conjunction. `#find` is also available as a command.\n`#find` will not affect the goal by itself and should be removed from the finished proof.\n\nThere is also the `find` tactic which looks for lemmas which are `apply`able against the current\ngoal.\n\nExamples:\n```lean\n#find _ + _ = _ + _\n#find ?n + _ = _ + ?n\n#find (_ : Nat) + _ = _ + _\n#find Nat → Nat\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.«tactic#find_»","kind":"def","line":146,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Find.«tactic#find_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/Find.lean#L146-L166"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.tacticFind\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Find</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticFind</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`find` finds definitions and theorems whose result type matches the current goal exactly,\nand prints them as info lines.\nIn other words, `find` lists definitions and theorems that are `apply`able against the current goal.\n`find` will not affect the goal by itself and should be removed from the finished proof.\n\nFor a command or tactic that takes the type to search for as an argument, see `#find`.\n\nExample:\n```lean\nexample : True := by\n  find\n  -- True.intro: True\n  -- trivial: True\n  -- ...\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.tacticFind","kind":"def","line":126,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Find.tacticFind","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/Find.lean#L126-L144"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.«command#find_»\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Find</span>.<span class=\"name\">«command#find_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`#find t` finds definitions and theorems whose result type matches the term `t`, and prints them as\ninfo lines. Use holes in `t` to indicate arbitrary subexpressions, for example `#find _ ∧ _` will\nmatch any conjunction.\n\n`#find` is also available as a tactic, and there is also the `find` tactic which looks for lemmas\nwhich are `apply`able against the current goal.\n\nExamples:\n```lean\n#find _ + _ = _ + _\n#find ?n + _ = _ + ?n\n#find (_ : Nat) + _ = _ + _\n#find Nat → Nat\n```\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.«command#find_»","kind":"def","line":93,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Find.«command#find_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/Find.lean#L93-L113"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.findType\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Find</span>.<span class=\"name\">findType</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">t</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.findType","kind":"def","line":69,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Find.findType","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/Find.lean#L69-L90"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.findDeclsPerHead\"><span class=\"name\">Mathlib</span>.<span class=\"name\">Tactic</span>.<span class=\"name\">Find</span>.<span class=\"name\">findDeclsPerHead</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Util/Cache.html#Batteries.Tactic.DeclCache\">Batteries.Tactic.DeclCache</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Std/Data/HashMap/Basic.html#Std.HashMap\">Std.HashMap</a> <a href=\"./Lean/HeadIndex.html#Lean.HeadIndex\">Lean.HeadIndex</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Lean.Name</a>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Mathlib/Tactic/Find.html#Mathlib.Tactic.Find.findDeclsPerHead","kind":"opaque","line":59,"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Find.findDeclsPerHead","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Tactic/Find.lean#L59-L67"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Init","Batteries.Util.Cache","Lean.HeadIndex","Lean.Elab.Command","Batteries.Util.Cache"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Tactic.Find"}